snippet.title: Patriot Malayalam Teaser | Mammootty | Mohanlal | Mahesh Narayanan | Anto Joseph
snippet.description:
From Anto Joseph Productions, the banner behind some of the most acclaimed and celebrated films in recent times, and visionary filmmaker Mahesh Narayanan comes the Official Teaser of Patriot.

Featuring an ensemble of legends: Mammootty, Mohanlal, Fahadh Faasil, Kunchacko Boban, Nayanthara, and Revathy.

Watch Tamil Teaser: https://youtu.be/WfGTzc4TsU4

Produced by:  Anto Joseph, K G Anil Kumar
Co Produced by : C R Saleem, Subhash George Manuel
Music & Original Score  : Sushin Shyam 
Teaser music mixed- Abin paul
Director of Photography : Manush Nandan ISC
Executive producers: C V Sarathi, Rajesh krishna

snippet.title: Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Official Trailer | Nirvair Pannu | Bir Singh | In Cinemas on Oct 10
snippet.description:
Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya | Official Trailer | Nirvair Pannu | Bir Singh | In Cinemas on Oct 10

Set in Punjab during the 1990s, Soohe Ve Cheere Waleya is a soulful tale that bridges love, poetry, and history across borders. Nirvair Pannu (Sooba), a young man running a telephone shop near the Indo-Pak border, finds solace in the verses aired on Lahore Radio. Unknown to him, those poignant words belong to Naazo, a mute girl in Pakistan who expresses her voice through poetry while struggling with her family‚Äôs hardships. 
A twist of fate connects them when army wireless sets fall into their hands, creating a secret channel across the border. Amid deception, smuggling, and family struggles, Nirvair discovers that the mysterious poetess he has long admired is Naazo herself.
What follows is an emotional journey that not only unites two hearts but also revives the unfinished stories of Partition‚Äîwhere love, loss, and courage once redefined destinies.

Ho gaye hain hum teri kasam
Chuu ke jabse mehke tujhse

Tu jo mera toh main chahun is duniya se bhi kya ‚Ä¶.

Dono jahanon se badh ke tu mera hua 
Ishq muhanon pe dhadke tu mera hua

Kitani zubaanon pe chadh ke tu mera hua 

Antra

Yun kabhi Pahle ye dhadka hi nahin 
Seene mein jaise dil mere tha hi nhin 
Shamein bhi thi Kahin din mere the Kahin 
Tu Mila jis jagah reh Gaya main wahin 

Sau wajha thi mili kuch to thi par kami 
Kyun lage Pahle main jaise jiya hi nahin 

Tu jo mera toh main chahun is duniya se bhi kya ‚Ä¶.

Kitani zubaanon pe chadh ke tu mera hua

snippet.title: VALORANT Champions Paris ‚Äî Playoffs Stage ‚Äî Day 16
snippet.description:
Welcome to the climax of the 2025 VALORANT Champions Tour! The biggest stage in VALORANT is ready, the lights of Paris are shining, and the countdown has begun. Following a season of historic rivalries, epic comebacks, and unforgettable moments, the world‚Äôs top teams now gather at Champions Paris.

From September 12 to October 5, the journey continues through Group Stage and Playoffs before the epic conclusion at the Grand Final with the crowning of the next World Champion. The Group Stage will feature 16 teams spread across four groups, with each group hosting one team from VALORANT's four International Leagues. In this stage, teams will battle through a double elimination format, advancing two teams out of each group. The 8 teams who make it out will be randomly seeded into a double elimination bracket, with teams from the same group placed on opposite sides of the bracket. Teams will compete through Best-of-3 matches until the final 2 matches which will be a Best-of-5. The last team standing will claim the title of VALORANT World Champion!

We‚Äôre proud to work with our fantastic partners throughout 2025: AWS, Coinbase, EWC, HyperX, Mastercard, OMEN, Red Bull, Secretlab, and Verizon.

Make sure to follow the official VALORANT Esports social channels for additional information:
Twitter/X: @valorantesports
Facebook: /valorantesports
Instagram: @valorantesports
TikTok: @valorantesports
Twitch: https://www.twitch.tv/valorant
YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@ValorantEsports
Photos from the Event: https://www.flickr.com/photos/valorantesports/
Official VALORANT Esports News: https://valorantesports.com/news
Web: https://valorantesports.com
#VCT #VALORANTChampions

snippet.description:
Immerse yourself in the heartfelt world of Bollywood's sentimental classics. Lend your ears to 'Yeh Reshmi Zulfen (Revival)', a quintessential melody from 1969, beautifully rendered by the legendary Mohammed Rafi. This song remains a testament to the honey-filled tones, soul-stirring lyrics, and the deeply emotional delivery that defined his style. The melodic journey takes you back to the iconic Bollywood of the 1969s, a golden period filled with poetic compositions and passionate performances. 

Allow the magic of Mohammed Rafi's voice to fill your hearts in this revival of 'Yeh Reshmi Zulfen' from the album 'Revival Vol.13'. Dive deep into nostalgia and experience the timeless appeal of the Hindi film industry's most loved sentimental songs.

FEATURES

- Discover your favorite attacking army from countless combinations of troops, spells, Heroes and Clan reinforcements 
- Defend your village with a multitude of Cannons, Towers, Mortars, Bombs, Traps and Walls
- Fight against the Goblin King in a campaign through the realm

snippet.title: Takkar (Official Video) Masoom Sharma | Manish Gurjar, Fiza Choudhary | New Haryanvi Song 2025
snippet.description:
Takkar (Official Video) Masoom Sharma | Manish Gurjar, Fiza Choudhary | New Haryanvi Song 2025

Dollar Music presents new haryanvi song Takkar by Masoom Sharma & Ashu Twinkle ft. Manish Gurjar & Fiza Choudhary . Lyrics penned by Amar Karnawal. Music given by Pinna Music. Video by Mohan Betaab.


Song : Takkar
Singer : Masoom Sharma & Ashu Twinkle
Lyrics : Amar Karnawal
Starring : Manish Gurjar & Fiza Choudhary
Music : Pinna
Video : Mohan Betaab
Dop : Sushil Thind
AD : Vishal Kumar, Manjot Gill
Hair, Makeup : Honey Kalsi
Editor :  Somvir Parjapat
DI : Sahil Patter
Production : Rahul Sungroya
Costumes : Rampy Sharma
Still & Making : Jagmohan
Casting : Rekha Thakur
Design : Prince Pannu
Producer : Nvii Chhaniwala, Kapil Arora
Label : Dollar Music
Digital Partner : Bounce Digital
Online Promotions : GEET DIGITALS ( 9053553351 )
Special Thanks : Dheeraj Shayar, Prik Roast, Aman, Sethi, Tinku Chopra, Samii, Rahul Chahar

Lyrics : 
Na seeli denda hon laadle naal jigane ki,
Tere yaar ne kardi band bolti jaan zamane ki,
Re tere sir loga ke raule
Haande case luanda bole
Nyu te jada din koni reh ghee teri sakkar me ,
Goj me asle
Unme goli
Gundey gaadi me s boli
Gelya yaara ki s toli
Pcr se chakkar me
Re karde chale yar ujaad
Se thada asleya gela laad
R jisne chava de se paad
Aaj maari koi na takkar me

Shaitano ka raja hai tu
Duniya tujse khalti hai
Bhokaal khada ho jata hai 
Jab teri pistol chalti hai,
O maa ne gunda ni jaamya mai halaato ki galti hai
Par paschim se uttar bharat tak 
Tere yaar ki chalti hai,
R haale se delhi gudgama
Dekha Tera tama jhama
Kar rha kya t or drama
Haande kiske chakkar me
Goj me asle
Unme goli
Gundey gaadi me s boli
Gelya yaara ki s toli
Pcr se chakkar me
Re karde chale yar ujaad
Se thada asleya gela laad
R jisne chava de se paad
Aaj maari koi na takkar me

R kyukar chale se bulldojar
Chale yaar mere tu gujjar
Tere gela karnawalia
S jo badmasha ka tutor,
Hootar police k baaje ja se
Yaar tere peeke nache ja se
Hindi amar amar si sunke
Madam tu b maache ja se,
R honi nhi kise te rees
Yaar thari sunle aaj manish
Ghanta ki kadwa raakhi khees
Jo maane khud ne aakhar s
Goj me asle
Unme goli
Gundey gaadi me s boli
Gelya yaara ki s toli
Pcr se chakkar me
Re karde chale yar ujaad
Se thada asleya gela laad
R jisne chava de se paad
Aaj maari koi na takkar me

snippet.title: Tumse Behtar | Varun D, Janhvi K, Sanya M, Rohit S | Tanishk B, Arijit S, Manoj M | SSKTK
snippet.description:
You‚Äôve seen them dance, you‚Äôve seen them fall in love, now witness the heartbreak when love gets intertwined! Presenting ‚ÄòTumse Behtar‚Äô from ‚ÄòSunny Sanskari Ki Tulsi Kumari‚Äô, starring Varun Dhawan, Janhvi Kapoor, Sanya Malhotra and Rohit Saraf. Composed by Tanishk Bagchi and written by Manoj Muntashir, this beautiful song is sung by Arijit Singh.

#TumseBehtar #ArijitSingh #TanishkBagchi #SSKTK

Music Composer: Tanishk Bagchi
Lyricist: Manoj Muntashir
Singer: Arijit Singh
Music Producer: Tanishk Bagchi & Krishna Kishor
Woodwinds: Nikhil Ram
Keys: Navneeth, Anoop, Melvin
Male Chorus: Rahul, Sanjay, Abijith, Aston
Female Chorus: Kamalaja, Fathima, Nayansi, Aarthi
Arijit Singh's Vocals Recorded by: Sukanto Singha
Arijit Singh‚Äôs Recordings Managed by: Ashish Biswal
Mixed and Mastered by: Eric Pillai @ Future Sounds of Bombay
Assistant Mix Engineer: Michael Edwin Pillai @ Future Sounds of Bombay
Music Supervisor: Azeem Dayani and Varun Dhawan
Sr Associate Music Supervisor: Tanvi Asher
Jr Associate Music Supervisor: Vasundhara Misra
Music Team: Heer Kamdar

Dharma Productions & Mentor Disciple Entertainment present 
A Dharma Productions Film
Starring Varun Dhawan, Janhvi Kapoor, Sanya Malhotra, & Rohit Saraf
Directed by Shashank Khaitan
Produced by Hiroo Yash Johar, Karan Johar, Adar Poonawalla, Apoorva Mehta & Shashank Khaitan
Co-produced by Marijke deSouza 
Written by Shashank Khaitan
Dialogues by Shashank Khaitan & Ishita Moitra

Lyrics:
Tumhara-mera milna likha to hoga kahin
Naseebon ka sitara, mila to hoga Kahin

Na Jane kyun ae humnasheen
Hai mere dil ko ye yaqeen
Ki tum sang ho to, bigdi baatein, saari ban jayengi
Tum jo has do, roothi raatein saari man jayengi

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Raaton me, bina tumhare ghabrayein, ghabraayein
Khwaabon me, milo agar khush ho jaayein ho jaayein

Chain ho tum aaram ho shayad
Koi sukoon ki shaam ho shayad
Khushi kahoon ya dil ki tasalli
Kya tumhein doon main naam

Kitabein dekhi saari, mili na koi shaayri
Tareefein karoon kaise, yahi hai muhskil meri

Na Jane kyun a humnasheen
Hai mere dil ko ye yaqeen
Ki tum sang ho to, bigdi baatein, saari ban jayengi
Tum jo has do, roothi raatein saari man jayengi
Jo daraeyin wo hawayein gham ki, tham jayengi

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Dekho na ye kamaal hua hai
Aesa dil ka haal hua hai
Dil mera tere itar me dooba
Jaise koi roomal hua hai

Aesi hai khwahish dil me mere
Jaane mujhe sab naam se tere
Aesi diwangi pahle nahin thee
Haal ye pichhle saal hua hai

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin
Aasmaa pe, tumse roshan, tara koi nahin!

Koi nahin tumse behtar, tumse pyaara
Tumse zyaada mera koi nahin!

Jo daraeyin wo hawayein gham ki, tham jayengi

Aesa dil ka haal hua hai

Jaane mujhe sab naam se tere
Aesi diwangi pahle nahin thee
Haal ye pichhle saal hua hai

Tumse behtar, tumse pyara yaara koi nahin

snippet.description:
Step back in time and revisit the classic love anthems of the 1977s. This musical journey highlights the golden era of Hindi cinema with unique renditions by the legends Kishore Kumar, Lata Mangeshkar, and Mohammed Rafi. In focus, 'Chal Kahin Door Nikal Jayen' from 'Doosara Aadmi' is a song that perfectly captures the essence of Love and Romance. Let's relive those times and immerse ourselves in the magical melodies of yesteryears.

Chapter list:

Leave your heart behind and dive into this beautiful world of love and music.
